<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-5068] CI is broken due to http://repo1.maven.org</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-5068</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Upstream has &lt;a href=&quot;https://support.sonatype.com/hc/en-us/articles/360041287334&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;removed&lt;/a&gt; support for HTTP based access. I&apos;ve &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/thrift/commit/70c4e7a7c7b2a2b4146372868702b7ea0d143e05&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;updated&lt;/a&gt; all references I could find, but the build is &lt;a href=&quot;https://travis-ci.org/apache/thrift/builds/637642594&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;still broken&lt;/a&gt; as we somehow still have references to the HTTP endpoint.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=jensg&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;jensg&quot;&gt;jensg&lt;/a&gt; any ideas?&lt;/p&gt;</description>
